{{For|other meanings of "Code" or "The Code"|Code (disambiguation)}}
{{Unreferenced|date=February 2008}}

The '''code of non-infringement''' (or '''"the Code"''') is the accepted business practice and [[convention (norm)|custom]] among certain [[performance art]]ists, particularly [[clown]]s, that an artist's unique performance attributes are [[Property|proprietary]] and cannot be used or claimed by another. Among clowns, these attributes may include [[stage name]]s, costume elements, facial designs, and clown's specific [[joke]]s or "gags" and "bits".

