{{Infobox company |name=Slamm Events |logo=[[Image:Slamm.png|250px|right]] |type=Private |foundation=March 19, 2006 |founder=Milton Felter and Maikel Polanen |location_country= |location_city=[[Almere]], [[Netherlands]] |key_people=Milton Felter, President |industry=Martial arts promotion |parent= |slogan= |homepage=http://slamm.nl/ }}
'''SLAMM!! Events''' was a [[Netherlands]] based [[mixed martial arts]] and [[thaiboxing]] promotion based in [[Almere]], Netherlands. They organized their flagship "Nederland vs Thailand" series, a ten-hour marathon of mixed martial arts and kickboxing fights<ref name=www.fightopinion.com>{{cite web|url=http://www.fightopinion.com/2008/03/09/slamm-nederland-vs-thailand-iv-road-report/|title=SLAMM!! "Nederland vs. Thailand IV" road report|accessdate=2008-09-08}}</ref> as well as an international events in [[Spain]], [[Belgium]], [[Italy]] and [[Suriname]]<ref name=sengokusite>{{cite web|url=http://slamm.nl/v1/?page=about&lang=nl |title=SLAMM!! OFFICIAL WEBSITE |accessdate=2008-09-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080914120343/http://www.slamm.nl/V1/?page=about |archivedate=September 14, 2008 }}</ref>
==Broadcast==
The Slamm events were delay broadcast to 52 countries on [[Eurosport]]<ref name="sengokusite"/>
==Rules==
Slamm [[Mixed martial arts|MMA]] fights were conducted under different rules from the North American [[Mixed martial arts rules|Unified Rules]]. Among the differences were the allowance of knees and stomps to the head of downed opponent. However elbows to the head and soccer kicks were prohibited. [[Muay Thai]] fights were conducted under full muay thai rules with elbows 5 X 3 rounds.
==Events== As of SLAMM: Nederland vs. Thailand VII, which occurred May 27, 2012, there have been 17 SLAMM events held.
